REQUIRES

One or more Wiegand readers, each connected to a pair of GPIO.

TO BUILD

gcc -Wall -pthread -o WD test_WD.c WD.c -lpigpiod_if2

TO RUN

sudo pigpiod # If the daemon is not already running

then

./WD -g7 -w8 -s30 # Read Wiegand codes from GPIO 7/8 for 30 seconds.

or

./WD -g5 -w6  # Read Wiegand codes from GPIO 5/6 forever.

or

./WD -? # for options

WD returns two values for each read code.  The code, and the number of bits.

DOWNLOAD & INSTALL (pigpio)

http://abyz.co.uk/rpi/pigpio/download.html

